		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Portuguese Republic is a country in the Iberian Peninsula sandwiched between Spain and the Atlantic Ocean. It is the western most state of mainland Europe. Its territory also includes the Atlantic archipelagos (island groups) Azores and Madeira, both autonomous regions.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Throughout history Portugal was inhabited by Celtics, Phoenicians, Carthaginians, Romans, Visigoths and Islamic Moors. County of Portugal was established after the battle São Mamede in 1128. Kingdom of Portugal was later proclaimed in 1139. During the 15th and 16th century Portugal started the first global maritime empire. During this period known as “the Age of Discovery”, Portuguese explorers like Bartolomeu Dias sailed beyond the Cape of Good Hope in South Africa, Vasco de Gamma discovered the sea route to India, and Pedro Álvares Cabral discovered Brazil. Through global explorations, expansions to Americas and Asia, and monopolizing the spice trade, Portugal
 
became the biggest economic and political power in the world. However, after the 1755 Lisbon Earthquake (that took 30,000 lives and destroyed much of coastal towns with Tsunamis), Napoleonic Wars in early 1800s, and the independence of Brazil in 1822 greatly reduced Portugals economic wealth and colonial ambitions. In 1932 Antonio Salazar took power of the country as a prime minister creating the second Republic Estado Novo, however he ruled the country as a dictator for the next 42 years. In 1974 a left wing military took over the country and brought Democracy to Portugal and made dramatic changes including liberating Portugal’s African colonies.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="http://d279m997dpfwgl.cloudfront.net/wp/2011/09/0913_vasco_crop.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Vasco de Gamma discovered the sea route to India</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today Portugal is a peaceful, developed country with an advanced economy and high living standards. It is highly placed in the rankings of moral freedom, peacefulness, democracy and freedom of press. Portugal is also a founding member of NATO, and is a member of United Nations and the European Union.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Geographically Portugal is split into two regions by the Tagus River that flows from Spain through Lisbon and out to the Atlantic Ocean. The Northern landscape is mountainous, while the South including the coastal Algarve and Alentejo regions is mostly rolling plains. The archipelagos the Azores are in the Mid-Atlantic ocean ridge of the coast of Portugal, and Madeira is further down south in the Atlantic Ocean off the coast of Morocco.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/proxy/pkEsiCM3UgGd5hVuCCul04EhFpL9_bJ7Olb5O82x45lqFGU6ee0zL1f-SxjaITcj5vLHnoIhZeOga41_1TAIQi76UJVbo7Tq9v8xgqngkNxESItSL5QD9s1EtJieIfPZVTTVEM0AuFoKSmcHlafODGFJjxydpF2Z6s82">
