				Portugal is a surfer’s paradise with 800 kilometers (500 miles) of dramatic coast line. Praia do Norte in Nazare, Portugal has some of the biggest waves ever encountered in the world. In 2013 a Brazilian surfer Carlos Burle took on a wave that was 29 meters high (95 feet). As tall as a ten story high building, it is believed to be the biggest wave ever surfed.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
